### â— Why it matters
Execution of scripts from user-writable locations (like Downloads) with bypass flags is a common technique to run unauthorized code and often precedes persistence or additional tooling deployment.

### ğŸ” KQL Query Used
```kql
DeviceProcessEvents
| where DeviceName == "sys1-dept"
| where FileName =~ "powershell.exe"
| where ProcessCommandLine contains "Downloads"
| project Timestamp, AccountName, ProcessCommandLine
| order by Timestamp asc
